choices.text:
Lazaro Soares application for the 2008 Nobel Prize for Peace after Renamo destroyed almost half of the World Heritage Site Irdreriru. Specific merits such as saving lives and protecting cultural heritage values were established.

Further, Lazaro Soares has given his reason for nomination as a Citizen of Working Class from a country suffering exposure to so much hardship through years of war and desperate social conditions.

The following points are presented in brief

i) Remedial treatment after civil war,

ii) Achievements on education,

iii) Current situation of elderly citizens,

iv) Contradiction in the case of Professor Ricardo Boese on Irideri, and

v) Protection of cultural heritage sites.

Dili/Kupang 9 September 2011

LENE RIENE LEON

(REDUC Case Officer)*

NOTE: The KPKL Irderiu campaign was formed to campaign KPKL protection in the former capital of East Timor, Dili - in the lead-up to the International meeting of UNESCO to discuss the destruction and tourism development of the dis area around KPKL Irderiu. At the same time Lazaro Soares submitted a nomination for the 2011 Nobel Peace Prize based on remedial treatment as a result of the war and protection of the KPKL in Dili (1999-2009).
